      "generics": [],
      "methods": [],
      "name": "druid.text.style",
    },
    {
      "brief": 
"Basic Druid text component. Text components by default have the text size adjusting.

### Setup
Create text node with druid: \`text = druid:new_text(node_name, [initial_value], [text_adjust_type])\`

### Notes
- Text component by default have auto adjust text sizing. Text never will be bigger, than text node size, which you can setup in GUI scene.
- Text pivot can be changed with \`text:set_pivot\`, and text will save their position inside their text size box
- There are several text adjust types:
-   - **"downscale"** - Change text's scale to fit in the text node size (default)
-   - **"trim"** - Trim the text with postfix (default - "...") to fit in the text node size
-   - **"no_adjust"** - No any adjust, like default Defold text node
-   - **"downscale_limited"** - Change text's scale like downscale, but there is limit for text's scale
-   - **"scroll"** - Change text's pivot to imitate scrolling in the text box. Use with stencil node for better effect.
-   - **"scale_then_scroll"** - Combine two modes: first limited downscale, then scroll
-   - **"trim_left"** - Trim the text with postfix (default - "...") to fit in the text node size
-   - **"scale_then_trim"** - Combine two modes: first limited downscale, then trim
-   - **"scale_then_trim_left"** - Combine two modes: first limited downscale, then trim left"
,
      "extends": "druid.component",
      "fields": [
        {
          "doc": "The text node",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "node",
          "types": [
            "node",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "fun(self: druid.text, text: string) The event triggered when the text is set",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "on_set_text",
          "types": [
            "event",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "fun(self: druid.text, scale: vector3, metrics: table) The event triggered when the text scale is updated",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "on_update_text_scale",
          "types": [
            "event",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "fun(self: druid.text, pivot: userdata) The event triggered when the text pivot is set",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "on_set_pivot",
          "types": [
            "event",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "The style of the text",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "style",
          "types": [
            "druid.text.style",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "The start pivot of the text",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "start_pivot",
          "types": [
            "number",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "The start scale of the text",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "start_scale",
          "types": [
            "vector3",
          ],
        },
        {
          "doc": "The current scale of the text",
          "isOptional": false,
          "name": "scale",
          "types": [
            "vector3",
          ],
        },
      ],
      "generics": [],
      "methods": [
        {
          "brief": "The Text constructor",
          "generics": [],
          "name": "init",
          "params": [
            {
              "doc": "Node name or GUI Text Node itself",
              "isOptional": false,
              "isVararg": false,
              "name": "node",
              "types": [
                "string|node",
              ],
            },
            {
              "doc": "Initial text. Default value is node text from GUI scene. Default: nil",
              "isOptional": false,
              "isVararg": false,
              "name": "value",
              "types": [
                "string|nil",
              ],
            },
            {
              "doc": "Adjust type for text. By default is "downscale". Options: "downscale", "trim", "no_adjust", "downscale_limited", "scroll", "scale_then_scroll", "trim_left", "scale_then_trim", "scale_then_trim_left"",
              "isOptional": false,
              "isVararg": false,
              "name": "adjust_type",
              "types": [
                "druid.text.adjust_type|nil",
              ],
            },
          ],
          "returns": [],
        },
        {
          "brief": "",
